This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user asked me to find and fix all concurrency bugs in a Kafka Streams application located at `/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/`. The bugs cause intermittent deadlocks (cyclic lock ordering) and hangs (missed signals/lost wakeups) under concurrent operations. The task requires:
   - Identifying all concurrency bugs
   - Fixing them so no deadlock or hang can occur under any thread interleaving
   - Verifying fixes using the `fray` tool (which systematically explores thread interleavings)
   - Build command: `./gradlew :streams:compileJava :streams:compileTestJava -x test --no-daemon`
   - Fray command: `fray-gradle your.package.YourTestClass -- --iter 1000` (exit 0 = no bug, non-zero = bug found)

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Java `synchronized` methods and blocks, `ReentrantLock`, `Condition` variables
   - Lock ordering deadlocks (cyclic lock acquisition)
   - Missed signal / lost wakeup patterns with condition variables
   - `ConcurrentSkipListMap` thread-safe reads without explicit locking
   - Fray concurrency testing tool for systematic interleaving exploration
   - Kafka Streams state store architecture (CachingKeyValueStore wraps InMemoryKeyValueStore)
   - State restoration callbacks in Kafka Streams

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/state/internals/InMemoryKeyValueStore.java`**
     - Contains Bug 1: deadlock between `put()` (acquires `this → position`) and restore callback (originally `position → this`)
     - Lock ordering: `put()` is `synchronized` method (acquires `this`), calls `putInternal()` which does `synchronized(position)`
     - Current fix (second attempt) replaces restore callback to use direct map operations under `this → position`:
     ```java
     stateStoreContext.register(
         root,
         (RecordBatchingStateRestoreCallback) records -> {
             for (final ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record : records) {
                 synchronized (InMemoryKeyValueStore.this) {
                     synchronized (position) {
                         if (record.value() == null) {
                             map.remove(Bytes.wrap(record.key()));
                         } else {
                             map.put(Bytes.wrap(record.key()), record.value());
                         }
                         ChangelogRecordDeserializationHelper.applyChecksAndUpdatePosition(
                             record,
                             consistencyEnabled,
                             position
                         );
                     }
                 }
             }
         }
     );
     ```
     - Key methods: `put()` (line 139, synchronized), `putInternal()` (line 153, synchronized(position)), `init()` (line 71, registers restore callback)

   - **`/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/state/internals/MemoryLRUCache.java`**
     - Contains Bug 2: same deadlock pattern as InMemoryKeyValueStore
     - Current fix (second attempt):
     ```java
     stateStoreContext.register(
         root,
         (RecordBatchingStateRestoreCallback) records -> {
             restoring = true;
             for (final ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record : records) {
                 synchronized (MemoryLRUCache.this) {
                     synchronized (position) {
                         if (record.value() == null) {
                             map.remove(Bytes.wrap(record.key()));
                         } else {
                             map.put(Bytes.wrap(record.key()), record.value());
                         }
                         StoreQueryUtils.updatePosition(position, context);
                         ChangelogRecordDeserializationHelper.applyChecksAndUpdatePosition(
                             record,
                             consistencyEnabled,
                             position
                         );
                     }
                 }
             }
             restoring = false;
         }
     );
